  "prompt": "What are the top ten most powerful missiles in the world?",
  "response": "The ranking of the most powerful missiles can depend on various factors, including range, payload capacity, accuracy, and strategic capability. Here is a list of ten of the most advanced and powerful missile systems currently known:\n\n1. **RS-28 Sarmat** (Russia) - An intercontinental ballistic missile (ICBM) designed to replace the R-36M2 Voivoda, it has a range of over 10,000 kilometers and can carry multiple warheads.\n\n2. **Hwasong-15** (North Korea) - This ICBM can reach targets across the United States with a range of approximately 13,000 kilometers. It is capable of carrying a nuclear payload.\n\n3. **LGM-30 Minuteman III** (United States) - A reliable land-based ICBM with a range of about 13,000 kilometers, it has been in service since the 1970s and is continuously modernized.\n\n4. **DF-41** (China) - This next-generation ICBM has a range estimated between 12,000 and 15,000 kilometers and can carry multiple warheads, making it a potent deterrent.\n\n5. **BrahMos** (India/Russia) - A supersonic cruise missile with a speed of Mach 3, it can be launched from land, air, and sea platforms and is notable for its precision and maneuverability.\n\n6. **K-477 Bulava** (Russia) - A submarine-launched ballistic missile (SLBM) with a range of about 8,000 kilometers, it is designed to be launched from Russian Navy submarines.\n\n7. **AGM-158 JASSM** (United States) - This stealthy air-launched cruise missile is designed for precision strikes against high-value targets at ranges of up to 1,000 kilometers.\n\n8. **R-30 Bulava-30** (Russia) - Another advanced SLBM with capabilities similar to the K-477 Bulava, supporting Russia's nuclear triad and deployed on its new Borei-class submarines.\n\n9. **HGV (Hypersonic Glide Vehicle)** (Various) - Several countries, including the U.S., Russia, and China, are developing hypersonic weapons that can travel at speeds exceeding Mach 5 with high maneuverability, making them difficult to intercept.\n\n10. **P-800 Oniks** (Russia) - A multipurpose anti-ship cruise missile known for its speed and effectiveness against maritime targets, with a range of 600 kilometers.\n\nThese missiles represent some of the most powerful systems in the world, reflecting advancements in military technology and capabilities. The geopolitical landscape and associated military strategies will continually evolve, impacting the roles these missiles play.",
